SIMPLE: widowhood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Widowhood
<hw>Wid"ow*hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
state of being a widow; the time during which a woman is widow; also,
rarely, the state of being a widower.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Johnson clung to her memory during a <qex>widowhood</qex> of more
than thirty years.</q> <rj><qau>Leslie Stephen.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Estate settled on a widow.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧I 'll assure her of her <xex>widowhood</xex> . . . in all my
lands.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Widow-hunter</ent>⟦br⟧
